descript.abstract:
U.S. Counties represents the counties of the United States in the 50 states and the District of Columbia. It includes over 1,600 demographic attributes from ESRI Community Data.
This data set provides three feature classes. The base feature class is called esri_cnty and isn't generalized. The weighted centroids feature class is called esri_cnty_1. The centroids are weighted by the U.S. Block Centroids population distribution. Use the weighted centroids in report aggregation and spatial overlay operations. The generalized boundaries feature class is called esri_cnty_2. Use the generalized boundaries when creating study areas.
descript.purpose: U.S. Counties provides detailed boundaries that are consistent with the tract and state data sets and are effective at regional and state levels. Extensive analysis can be performed with the over 1,600 demographic attributes.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data (non-generalized feature classes): 1:100,000.

dataqual.logic: The data set is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format using either ESRI SDC Geoprocessing tools in ArcGIS.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials. This data set provides two levels of generalization.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: For unchanged Geographies, Block Group, Tracts, Counties, State and US: Copied the data sets from ArcGIS® 9.3.1 Business Analyst 2009. Removed all attributes but ID, NAME, STATE_NAME, ST_ABBREV, AREA, Shape, and Genshp (the generalized Shape attribute). For Changed Geograpies, CBSA, DMA, and Zip5 boundaries: Used the Jan 2010 Teleatlas release of these data sets. For all Geographies: Reprojected all the data layers to Web Mercator (Auxiliary Sphere) and then re-compressed them back into SDC format. Used a custom tool created in-house to generate a weighted centroid shapefile of this data set from U.S. Block Centroids. Using the SDC Geoprocessing tools converted that data to SDC format and joined the centroid SDC file to the data set on ID. Joined the ESRI Community Data attributes, which were exported out of our Data Production environment into SDC Table format, to the SDC file with the geographic data and rearranged the attributes into their final order.

horizpa.horizpar: The horizontal positional accuracy is 167 feet for the base feature class <data set name>. This feature class also has the highest horizontal positional accuracy.
